{"hash":"e915bacfdad63495e7b1ca2cbaa8ed4357b24c0d","data":{"markdownPage":{"id":"15b7be32a528a56e54395200d605c60b","title":"Eventstorming - Shopping Mall","description":"","path":"/business/","timeToRead":2,"content":"<h1 id=\"eventstorming---shopping-mall\"><a href=\"#eventstorming---shopping-mall\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Eventstorming - Shopping Mall</h1>\n<p>Performing EventStorming based on the given Shopping Mall Scenario</p>\n<h2 id=\"msaez-modeling-tool-access\"><a href=\"#msaez-modeling-tool-access\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>MSAEZ Modeling Tool Access</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Open the Chrome browser and go to <a href=\"https://www.msaez.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.msaez.io</a>.</li>\n<li>Click on the avatar icon in the upper right corner and login with your Github account.</li>\n<li>Click on the first item, EventStorming, from the NEW menu.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/d35919e8-3ff6-4a13-bccc-6935f4d87dbf\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"basic-scenario---order-and-order-cancellation\"><a href=\"#basic-scenario---order-and-order-cancellation\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Basic Scenario - Order and Order Cancellation</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Customer selects a product and places an order.</li>\n<li>When an order is placed, the delivery of the product begins.</li>\n<li>Upon completion of delivery, the stock quantity of the product decreases.</li>\n<li>The customer can cancel an order.</li>\n<li>When an order is canceled, the delivery is canceled as well.</li>\n<li>When the delivery is picked up, the stock quantity increases.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"eventstorming\"><a href=\"#eventstorming\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>EventStorming</h2>\n<h3 id=\"step-1-events-orange-color\"><a href=\"#step-1-events-orange-color\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 1: Events (Orange Color)</h3>\n<p>The first step of EventStorming involves attaching domain events based on the narrative (verbs).</p>\n<p>From the scenario, we can extract the following domain events:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Customer selects a product and places an order. -> OrderPlaced</li>\n<li>When an order is placed, the delivery of the product begins. -> DeliveryStarted</li>\n<li>Upon completion of delivery, the stock quantity of the product decreases. -> StockDecreased\nSimilarly, for the order cancellation process:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/f5270052-f6e8-4f2d-82dc-f134ad8e11d6\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-2-ccommands-sky-blue-and-actors-yellow\"><a href=\"#step-2-ccommands-sky-blue-and-actors-yellow\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 2. CCommands (Sky Blue) and Actors (Yellow)</h3>\n<p>Add commands (sky blue) and actors (yellow) that trigger domain events to the left of the event stickers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Label commands in the present tense, representing human interactions such as ordering and canceling an order.</li>\n<li>Identify personas and add actors to the left of commands.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/05681759-4115-42f8-8710-ca0f8f2e1e91\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-3-policy-lilac-color\"><a href=\"#step-3-policy-lilac-color\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 3. Policy (Lilac Color)</h3>\n<p>Add reactive tasks related to events as policies (domain policies) to the right of events.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Describe tasks to be performed sequentially according to the event.</li>\n<li>For example, \"When an order is placed, start the delivery\" becomes a policy.</li>\n<li>The extracted policies for events are modeled as follows:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/3221fabc-39d9-4d8b-ab0f-e14c4c1cb56e\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-4-aggregates-yellow\"><a href=\"#step-4-aggregates-yellow\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 4. Aggregates (Yellow)</h3>\n<p>Add aggregates with appropriate names between commands and events, representing the repository that triggers domain state changes.</p>\n<p>Name aggregates after the information repository of the respective service.</p>\n<p>Model aggregates to overlap similar state change stickers.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/6b66213a-f2de-48be-b3f2-5604507238bf\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-5-bounded-context\"><a href=\"#step-5-bounded-context\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 5. Bounded Context</h3>\n<p>Group stickers by team or submodule to delineate boundaries.</p>\n<p>Click on the 'dashed circle' icon in the palette to wrap stickers for each team.</p>\n<p>The model with bounded contexts for each team looks like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/eac4d230-0ec0-4afc-a414-39e4adbc85e3\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n<h3 id=\"step-6-context-mapping\"><a href=\"#step-6-context-mapping\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"icon icon-link\"></span></a>Step 6. Context Mapping</h3>\n<p>Stickers attached to events represent policies, which are business processes of other teams that react to events.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Move each policy to the bounded context of the owning department.</li>\n<li>Attach arrows from events to the moved policy stickers to establish context mapping.</li>\n<li>The model with applied context mapping looks like this:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"https://github.com/acmexii/demo/assets/35618409/a12fd84d-2a8c-4fc8-a4aa-ddf568b3de42\" alt=\"image\"></p>\n","sidebar":"started","next":"","prev":"","headings":[{"depth":1,"value":"Eventstorming - Shopping Mall","anchor":"#eventstorming---shopping-mall"},{"depth":2,"value":"MSAEZ Modeling Tool Access","anchor":"#msaez-modeling-tool-access"},{"depth":2,"value":"Basic Scenario - Order and Order Cancellation","anchor":"#basic-scenario---order-and-order-cancellation"},{"depth":2,"value":"EventStorming","anchor":"#eventstorming"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 1: Events (Orange Color)","anchor":"#step-1-events-orange-color"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 2. CCommands (Sky Blue) and Actors (Yellow)","anchor":"#step-2-ccommands-sky-blue-and-actors-yellow"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 3. Policy (Lilac Color)","anchor":"#step-3-policy-lilac-color"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 4. Aggregates (Yellow)","anchor":"#step-4-aggregates-yellow"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 5. Bounded Context","anchor":"#step-5-bounded-context"},{"depth":3,"value":"Step 6. Context Mapping","anchor":"#step-6-context-mapping"}]},"allMarkdownPage":{"edges":[{"node":{"path":"/templates-language/springboot-java-template/","title":"Spring Boot/Java Template"}},{"node":{"path":"/operation/ops-deploy-diagramming-advanced-pvc/","title":"Persistent Volume"}},{"node":{"path":"/operation/ops-deploy-diagramming-advanced-istio/","title":"Istio Mesh"}},{"node":{"path":"/operation/ops-deploy-diagramming-basic-objects/","title":"12st Mall Basic Deploy"}},{"node":{"path":"/operation/ops-deploy-diagramming-advanced-hpa/","title":"Automatic Scaling (HPA) Deployment"}},{"node":{"path":"/templates-language/python-template/","title":"Python template "}},{"node":{"path":"/templates-language/go-template/","title":"Go Template "}},{"node":{"path":"/operation/ops-deploy-diagramming-advanced-ingress/","title":"Ingress Deployment Model Design"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/google-drive-examples/","title":"Google Drive Examples"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/infrastructure-modeling/","title":"Infrastructure Modeling (Kubernetes)"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/k8s-modeling/","title":"K8s Deployment Modeling"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/on-prem-inst/","title":"Installing on-premise MSA-Easy"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/event-storming-tool/","title":"EventStorming"}},{"node":{"path":"/tool/si-gpt/","title":"Code Implementation with Chat